    • Method Detail

      • setCopyInternDirForWorkflowVersionChange

        public void setCopyInternDirForWorkflowVersionChange(boolean value)
        Set to true by persistor if the loaded workflow was saved in an old format so that a new save would convert all nodes into the new format. The node will then copy the content of the "internal" dir into temp and save it the next time the flow is saved. Most of times this flag is not set.
        Parameters:
        value - the copyInternDirForWorkflowVersionChange to set

      • saveAdditionalFactorySettings

        public void saveAdditionalFactorySettings(ConfigWO config)
        Saves additional settings of this instance. This method is called by the framework upon workflow save and may be overwritten by subclasses.

        This method is mainly used in a dynamic context, where node factories are defined through a different extension that generates a set of node factories and not just a single one. Most derived node factories will therefore not overwrite this method (e.g. none of the wizard-generated factories).

        Overrides:
        saveAdditionalFactorySettings in class NodeFactory<MissingNodeModel>
        Parameters:
        config - To read from.
